    "I am defective",
    "I am trapped",
    "I am out of control",
    "I am powerless, weak, vulnerable"
  ],
  "unlovable_belief": [
    "I am unlovable",
    "I am bound to be abandoned"
  ],
  "worthless_belief": [
    "I am worthless, waste"
  ],
  "intermediate_belief": "If I open up about my struggles, people will see me as weak or burdensome, so it's safer to keep things to myself. If I let people get close, I'll end up being rejected or hurt again. I have to protect myself by not expecting support from others.",
  "intermediate_belief_depression": "If I reach out or try to connect, it won't matter because nothing will change and I'll just end up feeling more alone. There's no point in trying because I'm destined to be isolated.",
  "coping_strategies": "The client tends to withdraw from social interactions and isolate themselves when distressed, which maintains feelings of loneliness and depression. They sometimes ruminate on negative thoughts and avoid new social situations out of fear of rejection. Recently, they have begun to seek support by talking to a friend about their mental health, which is a more adaptive coping attempt.",
  "situation": "Engaged in a conversation with a friend about mental health struggles.",
  "auto_thought": "I'm just burdening them with my problems. They're probably thinking less of me now.",
